.TH phoenixdkim2-sign 1 "PhoenixDKIM"
.SH NAME
.B phoenixdkim2-sign
\- DKIM2 message signer (test tool)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B phoenixdkim2-sign
\-\-key FILE \-\-domain D \-\-selector S \-\-mail\-from "<a@b>"
[\-\-alg rsa\-sha256|ed25519\-sha256]
[\-\-rcpt\-to "<c@d>"]...
[\-\-time N]
[\-\-orig FILE]
[\-\-recipe FILE]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B phoenixdkim2-sign
reads a message on standard input, signs it under the experimental DKIM2
profile (draft\-ietf\-dkim\-dkim2\-spec), and writes the message to standard
output with the new
.I Message\-Instance
and
.I DKIM2\-Signature
header fields prepended.  It exists to exercise the DKIM2 chain against interop
fixtures without standing up an MTA; the milter
.RI ( phoenixdkim (8),
.I DKIM2Mode )
is the production signing path.
.PP
With no
.I \-\-orig
or
.I \-\-recipe
the tool signs as the originator (adding
.I Message\-Instance
.IR m=1 )
or, when the input already carries a chain, as a plain re\-signer.  Given a
pre\-modification message or a ready\-made recipe it instead records a
.I DKIM2\-extended
modification: a new
.I Message\-Instance
carrying the current hashes and a reversible recipe reverting to the previous
instance.
.PP
This program is built only when PhoenixDKIM is compiled with experimental DKIM2
support
.RI ( WITH_DKIM2 ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I \-\-key FILE
PEM private key (RSA or Ed25519).  Required.
.TP
.I \-\-domain D
Signing domain, placed in
.IR d= .
Required.
.TP
.I \-\-selector S
Selector for the key's DNS record.  Required.
.TP
.I \-\-mail\-from "<a@b>"
The SMTP reverse\-path to bind in
.IR mf= .
Required.
.TP
.I \-\-alg rsa\-sha256|ed25519\-sha256
Signing algorithm.  Defaults to the algorithm inferred from the key.
.TP
.I \-\-rcpt\-to "<c@d>"
An SMTP forward\-path to bind in
.IR rt= .
May be repeated; delivery order is preserved.
.TP
.I \-\-time N
Signature timestamp as a Unix epoch.  Defaults to the current time.
.TP
.I \-\-orig FILE
The pre\-modification message (an
.IR .eml ).
The recorded recipe is the diff that reconstructs it from the message being
signed.  Selects the modifying re\-signer path.
.TP
.I \-\-recipe FILE
A ready\-made base64\-JSON recipe to place in
.IR r= ,
read from
.IR FILE .
Takes precedence over
.I \-\-orig
if both are given.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The message was signed.
.TP
.B 1
Signing failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error, or a key/message could not be read.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I phoenixdkim2-verify (1),
.I phoenixdkim (8),
.I phoenixdkim.conf (5)
